# math.bignum — pure-Simple bignum scaffold (`crypto-pure-simple-port`).
#
# Public re-export hub. Three layers, with a sharp CT split:
#
#   limb.spl    — base 2^30 / [i64] constants and single-limb arithmetic.
#   bignat.spl  — variable-length BigNat ([i64]) for *public* values
#                 (modulus parsing, key gen, GCD, mod inverse). Branches
#                 on length; never use on secret data.
#   fixed.spl   — fixed-length `Fixed { n, limbs }` for secret-dependent
#                 paths. Length is a public compile-time parameter; every
#                 loop runs `n` iterations; every branch decides on a mask
#                 wrapped through `rt_black_box`.
#
# Migration note: `mod_exp_ct` and `mod_inv_ct` now use a full modular
# reduction path in `fixed.spl`, so callers no longer depend on the old
# upper-half-truncation stub behaviour.

use std.math.bignum.limb.{
    LIMB_BITS, LIMB_BASE, LIMB_MASK,
    FIXED_256, FIXED_512, FIXED_2048, FIXED_4096
}
